Chicago Pacific Corp said it couldachieve the 1987 estimates of some analysts for a sharpincrease in sales and in fully diluted per share earningsbefore extraordinary items in 1987.    The company said the estimates ranged from 3.10 dlrs to3.40 dlrs per share and sales of more than 1.35 billion dlrs.    It earned 2.30 dlrs per share in 1986 on sales of 954.9 mlndlrs. Reuter&#3;